sentences.english: It also lets you search and compare results from two search engines side by side.

這樣微妙的並列是不可避免的。

sentences.english: And side by side, we're going to run another engine.

sentences.english: Metaphor and metonymy are treated as two different figures of speech in traditional rhetoric.

sentences.english: The inner part of the line clip is provided with at least two line clamping tunnels which are arranged in parallel.

sentences.english: A single pictorial composition made by juxtaposing or superimposing many pictures or designs.

sentences.english: He could not rank as yet with the magnates of the eastthe serried sequoias of wall street .

sentences.english: Something quite illogic, if these two juxtaposed reverse direction sewers are looked at within the same big picture.

sentences.english: Rather, the years pile on like blankets, existing all at once.
sentences.chinese: 這麼說吧，年份像毯子一樣堆疊，相互並列同時存在。

sentences.english: And list the Crodyceps having been discovered in this area during the past years.
